I strolled into El Pecado starved.. I had walked a bunch in the earlier period of the day without a meal and finally had to grab something. I seemed to land at the perfect place for tacos.. I mean ... chicken tacos.. real tacos! They were so good .. and I know when a persons starving foods much better tasting.. but I ordered 3 to go. And after trying the salsa de habanero on the first two I was good.. so I walked on ..  I knew they were too good.. when a guy and his family were asking for street help from folks with some spare cash. Or anything the sign said..  So I gave him the last taco and the change I had.. and I knew since they appeared latino or Hispanic.  .. that he was going to  love that taco. No matter how meager the offering.  And when I walked away..  My toungue dropped a tear. And my belly.. was good. So..  5 stars and see you soon. Thank you guys.. even though I came back in to say how good they were I still have to drop this review for yall.  Yummy

So when I first tried this place it was awesome and gave it a five star review.. then later changed it to four. Based on our last night's experience  (pick up) I am changing it to two stars, though I think I am being generous. My shrimp taco had no toppings, steak taco was all ground low quality meat and had chewy parts which I'd to spit out. Mexican rice was plain yellow rice without any vegs. in it. Beans had a funky smell which we did not pay much attention to at that time. Today when I opened up that bowl - full order of refried beans, it was already rotten!  This time when restaurants are struggling to survive, I'd hate to go to another restaurant, but hey, I don't want to waste my money or get sick if they do not care about their business. There are several Mexican restaurants on Clark street and around. I am definitely going to try another place next time.

Ordered steak tacos & was served what looks like to me is ground beef, Not steak..brought it to the cashiers attention & she stated that the steak was just chopped up very fine & that their ground beef is different ....Hmmmmm I’m not one to return food to the cook, due to fear of something nasty happening to new food. So I ate the tacos... would’ve given them 0 or 1 star, but the “groundbeef” tacos were pretty good. The steak meat needs to be more defined, cause this sure looks like ground beef to me.
